00:23:15.000 --> 00:23:17.000
TO EACH OTHER AND I THINK THAT

00:23:17.000 --> 00:23:19.000
THERE IS A LOVE THERE THAT MAY

00:23:19.000 --> 00:23:20.000
BE AS PROFOUND AND AS DEEP,

00:23:20.000 --> 00:23:22.000
THOUGH OF A DIFFERENT QUALITY

00:23:22.000 --> 00:23:24.000
THAN THE ROMANTIC ENCHANTMENT

00:23:24.000 --> 00:23:25.000
THAT WE FIND WHEN WE'RE 18.

00:23:25.000 --> 00:23:27.000
Reporter: ALI HASSAN,

00:23:27.000 --> 00:23:28.000
A PREMED STUDENT, NOW STUDYING

00:23:28.000 --> 00:23:30.000
IN NEBRASKA, WAS TOLD

00:23:30.000 --> 00:23:31.000
BY HIS PARENTS LAST YEAR, THEY'D

00:23:31.000 --> 00:23:32.000
FOUND A BRIDE FOR HIM

00:23:32.000 --> 00:23:34.000
IN PAKISTAN.

00:23:34.000 --> 00:23:36.000
IF HE MARRIED HER, THEY SAID, IT

00:23:36.000 --> 00:23:37.000
WOULD HELP END A FAMILY FEUD.

00:23:37.000 --> 00:23:38.000
ALI DISCUSSED THIS

00:23:38.000 --> 00:23:40.000
WITH HIS FRIENDS AT SCHOOL.

00:23:40.000 --> 00:23:41.000
AND THEY, I UNDERSTAND, SAID

00:23:41.000 --> 00:23:43.000
TO YOU, "ARE YOU NUTS?"

00:23:43.000 --> 00:23:44.000
THEY WERE LIKE, "THIS IS

00:23:44.000 --> 00:23:45.000
A VIOLATION OF YOUR BASIC HUMAN

00:23:45.000 --> 00:23:46.000
RIGHTS."

00:23:46.000 --> 00:23:47.000
THEY WERE GIVING ME ALL THESE

00:23:47.000 --> 00:23:49.000
THINGS --

00:23:49.000 --> 00:23:50.000
Reporter: HE FLEW TO PAKISTAN

00:23:50.000 --> 00:23:51.000
AND MARRIED THIS 18-YEAR-OLD

00:23:51.000 --> 00:23:53.000
GIRL, WITHOUT EVER MEETING

00:23:53.000 --> 00:23:55.000
HER FIRST.

00:23:55.000 --> 00:23:55.000
I SAW HER HALF AN HOUR AFTER

00:23:55.000 --> 00:23:58.000
I WAS MARRIED.

00:23:58.000 --> 00:23:58.000
Reporter: YOU GOT MARRIED

00:23:58.000 --> 00:23:59.000
WITHOUT SEEING HER?

00:23:59.000 --> 00:24:01.000
YES, BECAUSE YOU SEE,

00:24:01.000 --> 00:24:03.000
THE CEREMONY WAS DONE IN A HOUSE

00:24:03.000 --> 00:24:03.000
THAT WAS DIVIDED BY A WOMEN'S

00:24:03.000 --> 00:24:04.000
SECTION OF THE HOUSE AND A MEN'S

00:24:04.000 --> 00:24:05.000
SECTION OF THE HOUSE.

00:24:05.000 --> 00:24:06.000
THEY MADE ME SIT DOWN.

00:24:06.000 --> 00:24:09.000
THEY MADE ME SIT DOWN,

00:24:09.000 --> 00:24:10.000
THEY INTRODUCED US, AND I LIKED

00:24:10.000 --> 00:24:10.000
HER A LOT, ACTUALLY.

00:24:10.000 --> 00:24:11.000
Reporter: WHAT -- WHAT DID

00:24:11.000 --> 00:24:13.000
YOU LIKE?

00:24:13.000 --> 00:24:15.000
SHE WAS GORGEOUS.

00:24:15.000 --> 00:24:17.000
I MEAN, SHE WAS ALL I WANTED --

00:24:17.000 --> 00:24:19.000
INNOCENT, VERY -- VERY, VERY,

00:24:19.000 --> 00:24:21.000
VERY EASTERN.

00:24:21.000 --> 00:24:23.000
AND THAT'S WHAT I WANTED.

00:24:23.000 --> 00:24:24.000
Reporter: IN A FEW YEARS

00:24:24.000 --> 00:24:26.000
SHE'LL JOIN HIM IN AMERICA.

00:24:26.000 --> 00:24:27.000
IF I DO FIND THINGS THAT ARE

00:24:27.000 --> 00:24:28.000
NOT GOOD ABOUT HER, I'M GOING

00:24:28.000 --> 00:24:28.000
TO COMPROMISE.

00:24:28.000 --> 00:24:29.000
I'M NOT GOING TO RUIN

00:24:29.000 --> 00:24:29.000
HER LIFE --

00:24:29.000 --> 00:24:31.000
Reporter: WHAT IF HE'S AWFUL?

00:24:31.000 --> 00:24:31.000
[ LAUGHTER ]

00:24:31.000 --> 00:24:32.000
WHAT IF SHE'S --

00:24:32.000 --> 00:24:34.000
HOW CAN -- SHE'S ONLY 18.

00:24:34.000 --> 00:24:36.000
HOW AWFUL CAN YOU GET AT 18?

00:24:36.000 --> 00:24:36.000
[ LAUGHTER ]

00:24:36.000 --> 00:24:38.000
Reporter: SHE COULD BE MEAN,

00:24:38.000 --> 00:24:40.000
SELFISH --

00:24:40.000 --> 00:24:41.000
I DON'T KNOW ABOUT THAT.

00:24:41.000 --> 00:24:42.000
ONLY TIME WILL TELL WHEN I'M

00:24:42.000 --> 00:24:44.000
WITH HER.

00:24:44.000 --> 00:24:44.000
Reporter: MOST HERE WERE

00:24:44.000 --> 00:24:46.000
SKEPTICAL OF AMERICAN DATING.

00:24:46.000 --> 00:24:49.000
SINIANG IS SINGLE AND LIVES

00:24:49.000 --> 00:24:51.000
NEW YORK.

00:24:51.000 --> 00:24:52.000
AND YOU SAY THE PURPOSE IS

00:24:52.000 --> 00:24:52.000
TO GET TO KNOW YOUR PARTNER,

00:24:52.000 --> 00:24:53.000
BUT WE NEVER REALLY DO

00:24:53.000 --> 00:24:55.000
BECAUSE IN THE DATING GAME

00:24:55.000 --> 00:24:56.000
WE TRY TO PUT UP THE BEST

00:24:56.000 --> 00:24:57.000
APPEARANCE THAT WE CAN.

00:24:57.000 --> 00:24:59.000
YOU ARE TRYING TO IMPRESS

00:24:59.000 --> 00:25:00.000
THE OTHER PERSON AND THAT'S NOT

00:25:00.000 --> 00:25:02.000
WHO WE REALLY ARE.

00:25:02.000 --> 00:25:04.000
SO, IT TAKES A WHOLE LIFETIME

00:25:04.000 --> 00:25:05.000
TO GET TO KNOW YOUR PARTNER.

00:25:05.000 --> 00:25:06.000
Reporter: WELL, HOW DO

00:25:06.000 --> 00:25:06.000
YOUR PARENTS KNOW?

00:25:06.000 --> 00:25:08.000
WE ARE THEIR KIDS

00:25:08.000 --> 00:25:09.000
AND THEY KNOW TEMPERAMENT.

00:25:09.000 --> 00:25:12.000
THEY KNOW WHAT'S BETTER FOR US.

00:25:12.000 --> 00:25:13.000
Reporter: SIMA KUKU SAYS

00:25:13.000 --> 00:25:14.000
HER AMERICAN FRIENDS AREN'T

00:25:14.000 --> 00:25:16.000
FINDING GOOD HUSBANDS BY DATING.

00:25:16.000 --> 00:25:17.000
BECAUSE THEY'RE NOT LOOKING

00:25:17.000 --> 00:25:18.000
AT THINGS THAT REALLY MATTER

00:25:18.000 --> 00:25:20.000
IN MARRIAGE.

00:25:20.000 --> 00:25:22.000
Reporter: SIMA GREW UP

00:25:22.000 --> 00:25:23.000
IN AMERICA AND AT AGE 27 GOT

00:25:23.000 --> 00:25:24.000
TIRED OF DATING AND LET

00:25:24.000 --> 00:25:26.000
HER IRANIAN PARENTS ARRANGE

00:25:26.000 --> 00:25:27.000
FOR HER TO MARRY AN IRAQI MAN,

00:25:27.000 --> 00:25:28.000
KELLY KUKU.

00:25:28.000 --> 00:25:30.000
THEY DECIDED TO MARRY AFTER

00:25:30.000 --> 00:25:32.000
DATING JUST THREE WEEKS.

00:25:32.000 --> 00:25:33.000
WE LIKED EACH OTHER AND IT

00:25:33.000 --> 00:25:35.000
JUST WORKED OUT THAT WE REALLY

00:25:35.000 --> 00:25:36.000
DID FALL IN LOVE.

00:25:36.000 --> 00:25:38.000
LOVE COMES.

00:25:38.000 --> 00:25:39.000
YOU, YOU -- YOU HAVE TO TEND

00:25:39.000 --> 00:25:41.000
TO IT.

00:25:41.000 --> 00:25:42.000
LOVE JUST DOESN'T COME LIKE

00:25:42.000 --> 00:25:43.000
THAT.

00:25:43.000 --> 00:25:44.000
Reporter: WHAT'S WRONG

00:25:44.000 --> 00:25:44.000
WITH THE AMERICAN WAY?

00:25:44.000 --> 00:25:45.000
YOU'RE CAREFULLY, YOU DATE A LOT

00:25:45.000 --> 00:25:46.000
OF PEOPLE.

00:25:46.000 --> 00:25:47.000
YOU DON'T, YOU DON'T LOOK

00:25:47.000 --> 00:25:48.000
FOR THE RIGHT THINGS

00:25:48.000 --> 00:25:48.000
IN A PERSON.

00:25:48.000 --> 00:25:49.000
IF IT'S SO GOOD THE AMERICAN WAY

00:25:49.000 --> 00:25:50.000
HOW COME YOU HAVE SUCH A HIGH

00:25:50.000 --> 00:25:52.000
DIVORCE RATE?

00:25:52.000 --> 00:25:53.000
Reporter: SHE HAS A POINT.

00:25:53.000 --> 00:25:54.000
THOUGH IT MAY BE THAT DIVORCE

00:25:54.000 --> 00:25:55.000
RATES ARE LOWER IN OTHER

00:25:55.000 --> 00:25:56.000
COUNTRIES BECAUSE DIVORCE THERE

00:25:56.000 --> 00:25:58.000
IS SO UNACCEPTABLE, IF NOT

00:25:58.000 --> 00:25:59.000
ILLEGAL.

00:25:59.000 --> 00:26:00.000
WOULDN'T IT BE BETTER

00:26:00.000 --> 00:26:01.000
IF WE COULD MARRY FOR LOVE

00:26:01.000 --> 00:26:06.000
AND FIND BETTER WAYS TO MAKEN JOHN STOSS

00:26:06.000 --> 00:26:08.000
WE BEGAN TONIGHT'S

00:26:08.000 --> 00:26:09.000
PROGRAM LOOKING AT THE HEAT THAT

00:26:09.000 --> 00:26:10.000
ERUPTS WHEN WE MEET THAT SPECIAL

00:26:10.000 --> 00:26:10.000
PERSON.

00:26:10.000 --> 00:26:11.000
THAT'S ALWAYS EXCITING AND OFTEN

00:26:11.000 --> 00:26:12.000
EASY.

00:26:12.000 --> 00:26:14.000
NOW THE TOUGH PART.

00:26:14.000 --> 00:26:16.000
AFTER LUST AND INFATUATION FADE,

00:26:16.000 --> 00:26:19.000
HOW DO YOU STAY IN LOVE?

00:26:19.000 --> 00:26:20.000
**

00:26:20.000 --> 00:26:23.000
THIS IS FOR US, MY DEAR.

00:26:23.000 --> 00:26:24.000
Reporter: JEFF AND JOY NOW

00:26:24.000 --> 00:26:25.000
BEGIN THEIR LIFE AS A MARRIED

00:26:25.000 --> 00:26:27.000
COUPLE.

00:26:27.000 --> 00:26:28.000
I LOVE YOU SO MUCH.

00:26:28.000 --> 00:26:31.000
Reporter: WILL THEY LAST?

00:26:31.000 --> 00:26:33.000
**

00:26:33.000 --> 00:26:37.000
HOW DO COUPLES STAY TOGETHER?

00:26:37.000 --> 00:26:39.000
HOW DO MARRIAGES MAKE IT

00:26:39.000 --> 00:26:41.000
THROUGH BETTER AND WORSE?

00:26:41.000 --> 00:26:43.000
I WAS TAKEN IN BY HER.

00:26:43.000 --> 00:26:46.000
WE WANTED TO BE TOGETHER.

00:26:46.000 --> 00:26:47.000
OKAY.

00:26:47.000 --> 00:26:47.000
VERY GOOD.

00:26:47.000 --> 00:26:51.000
VERY GOOD.

00:26:51.000 --> 00:26:53.000
HE SAID LET'S GET SPLICED.

00:26:53.000 --> 00:26:54.000
LET'S GET SPLICED.

00:26:54.000 --> 00:26:55.000
WHAT DO YOU THINK?

00:26:55.000 --> 00:26:55.000
[ LAUGHTER ]

00:26:55.000 --> 00:26:56.000
Reporter: THESE COUPLES SAY

00:26:56.000 --> 00:26:57.000
THEY'RE HAPPILY MARRIED.

00:26:57.000 --> 00:26:59.000
FRANK AND KAY SEVOLDY

00:26:59.000 --> 00:27:01.000
FOR 56 YEARS.

00:27:01.000 --> 00:27:02.000
PASSION THEY SAY IS WHAT BROUGHT

00:27:02.000 --> 00:27:04.000
THEM TOGETHER, BUT IT'S NOT WHAT

00:27:04.000 --> 00:27:05.000
KEPT THEM TOGETHER.

00:27:05.000 --> 00:27:07.000
NO, OUR MARRIAGE WASN'T

00:27:07.000 --> 00:27:08.000
ALWAYS FULL OF PASSION.

00:27:08.000 --> 00:27:09.000
AND I DON'T THINK ANYONE SHOULD

00:27:09.000 --> 00:27:10.000
EXPECT THAT.

00:27:10.000 --> 00:27:11.000
NO MARRIAGE CAN BE FULL

00:27:11.000 --> 00:27:12.000
OF PASSION ALL THE TIME.

00:27:12.000 --> 00:27:14.000
THAT'S AN ILLUSION.

00:27:14.000 --> 00:27:15.000
WE LIKE EACH OTHER

00:27:15.000 --> 00:27:16.000
AND IF YOU WANT TO USE

00:27:16.000 --> 00:27:17.000
THE MODERN WORD, WE LOVE EACH

00:27:17.000 --> 00:27:18.000
OTHER.

00:27:18.000 --> 00:27:19.000
WE HAVE PHYSICAL -- WE STILL

00:27:19.000 --> 00:27:19.000
HAVE A PHYSICAL ATTRACTION

00:27:19.000 --> 00:27:20.000
FOR EACH OTHER.

00:27:20.000 --> 00:27:22.000
[ LAUGHTER ]

00:27:22.000 --> 00:27:24.000
Reporter: BUT WHAT MAKES

00:27:24.000 --> 00:27:25.000
THESE MARRIAGES WORK SAY

00:27:25.000 --> 00:27:27.000
THE EXPERTS IS THE THIRD STAGE

00:27:27.000 --> 00:27:28.000
OF LOVE, ATTACHMENT.

00:27:28.000 --> 00:27:30.000
THIS IS THE STAGE THAT CAN LAST.

00:27:30.000 --> 00:27:33.000
A GOOD MARRIAGE IS LIKE

00:27:33.000 --> 00:27:34.000
AN ORIENTAL RUG WITH ALL KINDS

00:27:34.000 --> 00:27:35.000
OF PATTERNS IN IT.

00:27:35.000 --> 00:27:36.000
HERE'S ANOTHER ONE.

00:27:36.000 --> 00:27:38.000
THAT THESE PEOPLE HAVE BUILT

00:27:38.000 --> 00:27:39.000
TOGETHER, THAT DEEP SENSE

00:27:39.000 --> 00:27:40.000
OF CALM AND SECURITY AND PEACE

00:27:40.000 --> 00:27:41.000
THAT YOU HAVE WITH A LONG-TERM

00:27:41.000 --> 00:27:43.000
PARTNER.

00:27:43.000 --> 00:27:44.000
WHAT ELSE, DO YOU SEE,

00:27:44.000 --> 00:27:45.000
ANYTHING?

00:27:45.000 --> 00:27:46.000
Reporter: SUCH GOOD MARRIAGES

00:27:46.000 --> 00:27:47.000
USUALLY REQUIRE FIGHTING

00:27:47.000 --> 00:27:49.000
THROUGH TROUBLE.

00:27:49.000 --> 00:27:50.000
RIGHT AFTER VIRGINIA LEWIS

00:27:50.000 --> 00:27:52.000
MARRIED, 67 YEARS AGO, SHE HAD

00:27:52.000 --> 00:27:53.000
SECOND THOUGHTS.

00:27:53.000 --> 00:27:54.000
[ LAUGHTER ]

00:27:54.000 --> 00:27:57.000
I LOOKED AT HIM

00:27:57.000 --> 00:27:59.000
AND I THOUGHT, WHAT HAVE I DONE?

00:27:59.000 --> 00:28:02.000
I DON'T EVEN KNOW THIS MAN.

00:28:02.000 --> 00:28:03.000
WHAT HAVE I DONE?

00:28:03.000 --> 00:28:05.000
I DON'T EVEN KNOW IF I KNOW WHAT

00:28:05.000 --> 00:28:06.000
LOVE MEANS AT THIS MOMENT?

00:28:06.000 --> 00:28:09.000
AND SO THE TEARS BEGAN TO FLOW.

00:28:09.000 --> 00:28:10.000
THAT'S A --

00:28:10.000 --> 00:28:11.000
YEAH, YEAH.

00:28:11.000 --> 00:28:13.000
Reporter: VIRGINIA IS NOW 90.

00:28:13.000 --> 00:28:15.000
BOB'S 94 AND THEIR MARRIAGE,

00:28:15.000 --> 00:28:17.000
THEY SAY, IS GOOD.

00:28:17.000 --> 00:28:19.000
WHEN WE RETIRE AT NIGHT,

00:28:19.000 --> 00:28:23.000
WE GET IN BED LIKE A COUPLE

00:28:23.000 --> 00:28:23.000
OF TEASPOONS, AND HE PUTS

00:28:23.000 --> 00:28:25.000
HIS ARM AROUND ME

00:28:25.000 --> 00:28:26.000
AND HE CHUCKLES AND SAYS, "THIS

00:28:26.000 --> 00:28:28.000
IS -- THIS IS IT," YOU KNOW.

00:28:28.000 --> 00:28:31.000
AND I FEEL THIS IS WONDERFUL.

00:28:31.000 --> 00:28:32.000
* THE DREAM I KNOW

00:28:32.000 --> 00:28:35.000
CAN NEVER BE *

00:28:35.000 --> 00:28:36.000
Reporter: AND THIS COUPLE

00:28:36.000 --> 00:28:38.000
SAYS AFTER 44 YEARS OF MARRIAGE,

00:28:38.000 --> 00:28:40.000
THE BEST OF TIMES IS NOW.

00:28:40.000 --> 00:28:42.000
THERE IS GREAT STUFF AHEAD

00:28:42.000 --> 00:28:43.000
IF YOU STAY ON THE JOB,

00:28:43.000 --> 00:28:43.000
SO TO SPEAK.

00:28:43.000 --> 00:28:44.000
THE BEST.

00:28:44.000 --> 00:28:44.000
YEAH.

00:28:44.000 --> 00:28:45.000
THIS IS THE BEST PERIOD

00:28:45.000 --> 00:28:47.000
IN OUR LIFE.

00:28:47.000 --> 00:28:56.000
Reporter: YES, THAT'S

00:28:56.000 --> 00:28:57.000
HER LOVE MAP.

00:28:57.000 --> 00:29:00.000
I LOOKED ACROSS THE ROOM,

00:29:00.000 --> 00:29:03.000
THIS MAN ENTERED.

00:29:03.000 --> 00:29:07.000
TALL, DARK, I TOOK ONE LOOK

00:29:07.000 --> 00:29:08.000
AT HIM AND I SAID, "IF THAT

00:29:08.000 --> 00:29:09.000
MAN'S NOT MARRIED, HE'S GOING

00:29:09.000 --> 00:29:10.000
TO BE SOMEDAY AND TO ME,"

00:29:10.000 --> 00:29:12.000
AND TWO YEARS LATER, ALMOST

00:29:12.000 --> 00:29:14.000
TO THE DAY, WE WERE MARRIED.

00:29:14.000 --> 00:29:15.000
Reporter: SINCE THEN THERE

00:29:15.000 --> 00:29:16.000
HAVE BEEN TROUBLES.

00:29:16.000 --> 00:29:16.000
ALLEN SAYS YOU'VE GOT TO EXPECT

00:29:16.000 --> 00:29:18.000
THAT.

00:29:18.000 --> 00:29:19.000
READ MY LIPS --

00:29:19.000 --> 00:29:21.000
THERE'S GOING TO BE BAD TIMES

00:29:21.000 --> 00:29:22.000
AND SOMETIMES VERY SERIOUS BAD

00:29:22.000 --> 00:29:23.000
TIMES.

00:29:23.000 --> 00:29:24.000
Reporter: STEVE CHEATED

00:29:24.000 --> 00:29:26.000
ON JAYNE.

00:29:26.000 --> 00:29:29.000
IT WAS WRONG.

00:29:29.000 --> 00:29:30.000
I WOULD HAVE BEEN TOTALLY HURT

00:29:30.000 --> 00:29:31.000
FOR LIFE IF, IF THE SITUATION

00:29:31.000 --> 00:29:32.000
HAD BEEN REVERSED AND IT HAD

00:29:32.000 --> 00:29:33.000
BEEN JAYNE THAT HAD BECOME

00:29:33.000 --> 00:29:36.000
INVOLVED.

00:29:36.000 --> 00:29:38.000
WE MOVED PAST ALL OF OUR BIG,

00:29:38.000 --> 00:29:40.000
BIG PROBLEMS BY GOING AND HAVING

00:29:40.000 --> 00:29:44.000
MARRIAGE COUNSELING, PSYCHIATRY,

00:29:44.000 --> 00:29:45.000
THE CHURCH, GOING TO CLASSES

00:29:45.000 --> 00:29:46.000
AT THE CHURCH, FINDING OUT

00:29:46.000 --> 00:29:48.000
YOU'RE NOT ALONE.

00:29:48.000 --> 00:29:49.000
IT HAS BEEN TOUGH BUT WE HAVE

00:29:49.000 --> 00:29:50.000
PERSISTED.

00:29:50.000 --> 00:29:52.000
WE ARE NOW APPROACHING

00:29:52.000 --> 00:29:52.000
OUR 44th YEAR.

00:29:52.000 --> 00:29:54.000
YES.

00:29:54.000 --> 00:29:55.000
-- LOOK THROUGH.

00:29:55.000 --> 00:29:56.000
Reporter: ARE THERE COMMON

00:29:56.000 --> 00:29:57.000
THREADS THAT KEEP SUCH COUPLES

00:29:57.000 --> 00:29:59.000
TOGETHER?

00:29:59.000 --> 00:30:01.000
WHY DO SOME RELATIONSHIPS

00:30:01.000 --> 00:30:02.000
UNRAVEL AND WHEN THEY DO, IS

00:30:02.000 --> 00:30:03.000
THERE SOMETHING WE CAN DO

00:30:03.000 --> 00:30:06.000
ABOUT IT?

00:30:06.000 --> 00:30:07.000
OKAY.

00:30:07.000 --> 00:30:10.000
PRINT IT ALL OUT.

00:30:10.000 --> 00:30:11.000
Reporter: JOHN GOTTMAN IS

