00:30:38.000 --> 00:30:39.000
I FELT LIKE YOU WERE NOT

00:30:39.000 --> 00:30:40.000
SHARE, SO WHY SHOULD I?

00:30:40.000 --> 00:30:42.000
Reporter: HIS TEAM WATCHES

00:30:42.000 --> 00:30:43.000
FACIAL EXPRESSIONS, HEART RATES,

00:30:43.000 --> 00:30:44.000
SWEAT RATES, SECOND BY SECOND.

00:30:44.000 --> 00:30:46.000
THEY CATEGORIZE EVERY MOMENT

00:30:46.000 --> 00:30:47.000
OF AFFECTION, ANGER,

00:30:47.000 --> 00:30:49.000
DEFENSIVENESS.

00:30:49.000 --> 00:30:50.000
IT'S LIKE AN X-RAY

00:30:50.000 --> 00:30:52.000
OF THE RELATIONSHIP.

00:30:52.000 --> 00:30:54.000
GOTTMAN SAYS FOUR KINDS

00:30:54.000 --> 00:30:55.000
OF BEHAVIOR ARE PREDICTORS

00:30:55.000 --> 00:30:57.000
OF DIVORCE.

00:30:57.000 --> 00:30:58.000
HE CALLS THEM FOUR HORSEMEN

00:30:58.000 --> 00:31:00.000
OF THE APOCALYPSE.

00:31:00.000 --> 00:31:01.000
THE FIRST ONE IS CRITICISM, THEN

00:31:01.000 --> 00:31:02.000
DEFENSIVENESS.

00:31:02.000 --> 00:31:03.000
THE THIRD ONE IS CONTEMPT,

00:31:03.000 --> 00:31:08.000
THE FOURTH WITHDRAWAL.

00:31:08.000 --> 00:31:09.000
FOUR YEARS AGO FOR "20/20,"

00:31:09.000 --> 00:31:10.000
WE TAPED THIS COUPLE

00:31:10.000 --> 00:31:12.000
AS THEY WENT THOUGH THE PROGRAM.

00:31:12.000 --> 00:31:13.000
DOUG AND THERESA DICHTMAN WERE

00:31:13.000 --> 00:31:14.000
ASKED TO DISCUSS A FAMILY

00:31:14.000 --> 00:31:16.000
CONFLICT.

00:31:16.000 --> 00:31:18.000
I HAD NO IDEA DAD WAS EVEN

00:31:18.000 --> 00:31:19.000
COMING TO TOWN OR THEY WERE

00:31:19.000 --> 00:31:20.000
GOING TO A MARINERS GAME

00:31:20.000 --> 00:31:21.000
OR ANYTHING, BECAUSE HE DIDN'T

00:31:21.000 --> 00:31:25.000
TELL ME.

00:31:25.000 --> 00:31:25.000
NOW, HE HAS A VERY CRUCIAL

00:31:25.000 --> 00:31:26.000
DECISION TO MAKE HERE.

00:31:26.000 --> 00:31:28.000
HOW IS HE GOING TO RESPOND

00:31:28.000 --> 00:31:29.000
TO HER COMPLAINT?

00:31:29.000 --> 00:31:31.000
SHE DIDN'T INSULT HIM.

00:31:31.000 --> 00:31:32.000
SHE DIDN'T CALL HIM ANY NAMES.

00:31:32.000 --> 00:31:33.000
SHE DIDN'T SAY HE WAS

00:31:33.000 --> 00:31:33.000
IRRESPONSIBLE, THAT HE WAS A BAD

00:31:33.000 --> 00:31:35.000
PERSON.

00:31:35.000 --> 00:31:37.000
LET'S SEE HOW HE RESPONDS.

00:31:37.000 --> 00:31:38.000
WELL, THAT'S NOT TRUE,

00:31:38.000 --> 00:31:38.000
BECAUSE I TOLD YOU ON TUESDAY

00:31:38.000 --> 00:31:40.000
THAT WE WERE GOING

00:31:40.000 --> 00:31:41.000
TO THE MARINERS GAME ON MONDAY,

00:31:41.000 --> 00:31:42.000
BUT THAT WASN'T IMPORTANT ENOUGH

00:31:42.000 --> 00:31:44.000
FOR YOU REMEMBER, APPARENTLY.

00:31:44.000 --> 00:31:45.000
HE'S DEFENSIVE.

00:31:45.000 --> 00:31:47.000
HE DEFENDS HIMSELF.

00:31:47.000 --> 00:31:48.000
DENIES RESPONSIBILITY

00:31:48.000 --> 00:31:51.000
FOR WHATEVER HAPPENED, AND THEN

00:31:51.000 --> 00:31:52.000
HE IS SARCASTIC.

00:31:52.000 --> 00:31:53.000
WELL, THAT WAS PRETTY

00:31:53.000 --> 00:31:55.000
BRILLIANT TO ASK ME WHEN I'M

00:31:55.000 --> 00:31:56.000
IN BED, HALF ASLEEP.

00:31:56.000 --> 00:31:57.000
Reporter: HE'S CONTEMPTUOUS

00:31:57.000 --> 00:31:58.000
OF HER.

00:31:58.000 --> 00:32:01.000
HE PUTS HER DOWN.

00:32:01.000 --> 00:32:04.000
CONTEMPT IS A VERY CORROSIVE

00:32:04.000 --> 00:32:05.000
THING IN A MARRIAGE.

00:32:05.000 --> 00:32:07.000
IT OUGHT REALLY TO BE OUTLAWED

00:32:07.000 --> 00:32:08.000
AND BANNED IN MARRIAGES.

00:32:08.000 --> 00:32:09.000
Reporter: HOW MUCH

00:32:09.000 --> 00:32:09.000
OF YOUR FOUR HORSEMEN DO YOU SEE

00:32:09.000 --> 00:32:10.000
IN THEM?

00:32:10.000 --> 00:32:13.000
I SEE THREE.

00:32:13.000 --> 00:32:14.000
THREE OUT OF THE FOUR --

00:32:14.000 --> 00:32:16.000
CRITICISM, CONTEMPT,

00:32:16.000 --> 00:32:19.000
DEFENSIVENESS.

00:32:19.000 --> 00:32:20.000
OH, ALL RIGHT!

00:32:20.000 --> 00:32:21.000
[ CHEERS ]

00:32:21.000 --> 00:32:22.000
Reporter: GOTTMAN PREDICTED

00:32:22.000 --> 00:32:22.000
THE DICHTMANS WOULD DIVORCE,

00:32:22.000 --> 00:32:23.000
BUT THE DICHTMANS DIDN'T BELIEVE

00:32:23.000 --> 00:32:24.000
IT.

00:32:24.000 --> 00:32:25.000
WILL YOU STAY MARRIED, DO

00:32:25.000 --> 00:32:26.000
YOU THINK?

00:32:26.000 --> 00:32:28.000
YEAH, WE'LL STAY MARRIED.

00:32:28.000 --> 00:32:30.000
Reporter: DO YOU LOVE HIM?

00:32:30.000 --> 00:32:30.000
YES, I LOVE HIM VERY MUCH.

00:32:30.000 --> 00:32:34.000
[ CHEERS ]

00:32:34.000 --> 00:32:35.000
Reporter: TWO YEARS LATER,

00:32:35.000 --> 00:32:36.000
THE DICHTMANS DID DIVORCE.

00:32:36.000 --> 00:32:38.000
DOUG NOW SAYS HE WISHED GOTTMAN,

00:32:38.000 --> 00:32:39.000
INSTEAD OF MAKING NEGATIVE

00:32:39.000 --> 00:32:40.000
PREDICTIONS, HAD ACTUALLY TRIED

00:32:40.000 --> 00:32:47.000
TO HELP.

00:32:47.000 --> 00:32:51.000
-- IT GOES DEEPER.

00:32:51.000 --> 00:32:52.000
Reporter: AND NOW GOTTMAN

00:32:52.000 --> 00:32:53.000
AND HIS WIFE, PSYCHOLOGIST

00:32:53.000 --> 00:32:54.000
JULIE GOTTMAN, DO HELP.

00:32:54.000 --> 00:32:55.000
TO SEE HOW, WE ARRANGED FOR THIS

00:32:55.000 --> 00:32:55.000
COUPLE DAN AND ALLISON KNITTEL

00:32:55.000 --> 00:32:56.000
TO GO THROUGH HIS MARRIAGE LAB.

00:32:56.000 --> 00:32:57.000
DAN IS AN ELECTRICAL ENGINEER

00:32:57.000 --> 00:32:57.000
IN THE NAVY, WORKING

00:32:57.000 --> 00:32:59.000
ON SUBMARINES.

00:32:59.000 --> 00:33:02.000
GO.

00:33:02.000 --> 00:33:02.000
Reporter: ALLISON IS

00:33:02.000 --> 00:33:03.000
A DISPATCHER FOR A LOCAL BUS

00:33:03.000 --> 00:33:04.000
SYSTEM.

00:33:04.000 --> 00:33:05.000
THEY MARRIED TWO YEARS AGO

00:33:05.000 --> 00:33:07.000
AND ANSWERED THE AD, EVEN THOUGH

00:33:07.000 --> 00:33:08.000
THEY DIDN'T THINK THEIR MARRIAGE

00:33:08.000 --> 00:33:10.000
WAS IN TROUBLE.

00:33:10.000 --> 00:33:12.000
THE KNITTELS STRUCK US AS A VERY

00:33:12.000 --> 00:33:13.000
CLOSE COUPLE.

00:33:13.000 --> 00:33:15.000
THEY'RE ALL OVER EACH, OTHER

00:33:15.000 --> 00:33:16.000
MUCH OF THE TIME.

00:33:16.000 --> 00:33:18.000
OF COURSE THEY HAVE CONFLICTS.

00:33:18.000 --> 00:33:20.000
IN THE LAB, DAN SUGGESTS

00:33:20.000 --> 00:33:21.000
THEY SAVE MONEY BY SELLING

00:33:21.000 --> 00:33:23.000
THEIR HOUSE AND MOVING

00:33:23.000 --> 00:33:24.000
INTO A TRAILER.

00:33:24.000 --> 00:33:25.000
THEN WHEREVER OUR JOBS TAKE

00:33:25.000 --> 00:33:27.000
US, AT LEAST WE GOT OUR HOME.

00:33:27.000 --> 00:33:28.000
MM-HMM.

00:33:28.000 --> 00:33:29.000
YOU KNOW, WE CAN GO THERE,

00:33:29.000 --> 00:33:30.000
YOU KNOW, EVEN IF WE HAVE TO SIT

00:33:30.000 --> 00:33:30.000
IN A TRAILER PARK FOR, YOU KNOW,

00:33:30.000 --> 00:33:31.000
MONTHS UNTIL WE CAN FIND

00:33:31.000 --> 00:33:33.000
SOMEPLACE TO LIVE.

00:33:33.000 --> 00:33:34.000
MY BIGGEST FEAR IS THAT ONCE

00:33:34.000 --> 00:33:35.000
WE GET INTO THAT LIFESTYLE

00:33:35.000 --> 00:33:38.000
WE WON'T GET OUT OF IT.

00:33:38.000 --> 00:33:39.000
Reporter: ON THE SURFACE

00:33:39.000 --> 00:33:40.000
THERE DOESN'T SEEM TO BE MUCH

00:33:40.000 --> 00:33:42.000
WRONG, BUT AS THE RESEARCHERS

00:33:42.000 --> 00:33:43.000
WATCH, THEY SEE DAN

00:33:43.000 --> 00:33:44.000
AND ALLISON'S HEART AND SWEAT

00:33:44.000 --> 00:33:46.000
RATES STAY LOW.

00:33:46.000 --> 00:33:49.000
THAT SUGGESTS THE FOURTH

00:33:49.000 --> 00:33:52.000
HORSEMAN, EMOTIONAL WITHDRAWAL.

00:33:52.000 --> 00:33:54.000
SO, WHAT DO WE DO?

00:33:54.000 --> 00:33:54.000
Reporter: SHE LOOKS

00:33:54.000 --> 00:33:55.000
AS IF SHE HAS CHECKED OUT.

00:33:55.000 --> 00:33:57.000
THAT'S RIGHT.

00:33:57.000 --> 00:33:59.000
YOU'RE PICKING THAT UP.

00:33:59.000 --> 00:34:01.000
SHE'S SITTING BACK.

00:34:01.000 --> 00:34:01.000
SHE'S NOT EVEN REALLY PAYING

00:34:01.000 --> 00:34:03.000
FULL ATTENTION TO HIM.

00:34:03.000 --> 00:34:06.000
SHE'S NOT THERE EMOTIONALLY.

00:34:06.000 --> 00:34:07.000
IF YOU TAKE A LOOK AT WHAT'S

00:34:07.000 --> 00:34:08.000
GOING ON UNDERNEATH, THEY'RE

00:34:08.000 --> 00:34:10.000
REALLY SAYING, I'M OUT OF THIS

00:34:10.000 --> 00:34:12.000
MARRIAGE.

00:34:12.000 --> 00:34:13.000
Reporter: THE RESEARCHERS GET

00:34:13.000 --> 00:34:15.000
MORE CLUES ABOUT THE SEEMINGLY

00:34:15.000 --> 00:34:16.000
BLISSFUL MARRIAGE

00:34:16.000 --> 00:34:18.000
FROM THE MARRIAGE QUESTIONNAIRE,

00:34:18.000 --> 00:34:20.000
ON WHICH ALLISON SAID SHE THINKS

00:34:20.000 --> 00:34:22.000
ABOUT DIVORCE OFTEN, SOMETIMES

00:34:22.000 --> 00:34:23.000
WISHES SHE HAD NEVER MARRIED.

00:34:23.000 --> 00:34:25.000
DAN, HOWEVER, SAYS HE'S

00:34:25.000 --> 00:34:27.000
PERFECTLY HAPPY.

00:34:27.000 --> 00:34:29.000
IT'S LIKE YOU ARE OUT TO LUNCH

00:34:29.000 --> 00:34:31.000
IN THE MARRIAGE HERE.

00:34:31.000 --> 00:34:32.000
SHE HAS ALL THESE THINGS SHE'S

00:34:32.000 --> 00:34:34.000
UNHAPPY ABOUT AND YOU SAY, "OH,

00:34:34.000 --> 00:34:35.000
MARRIAGE IS BLISS."

00:34:35.000 --> 00:34:39.000
WHERE ARE YOU?

00:34:39.000 --> 00:34:40.000
I DO --

00:34:40.000 --> 00:34:41.000
I DO A VERY GOOD JOB OF TRYING

00:34:41.000 --> 00:34:43.000
TO COVER MY EMOTIONS.

00:34:43.000 --> 00:34:45.000
A SCORE OF FOUR ON THIS

00:34:45.000 --> 00:34:48.000
DIVORCE POTENTIAL SCALE SUGGESTS

00:34:48.000 --> 00:34:49.000
THAT IT'S VERY LIKELY THAT THIS

00:34:49.000 --> 00:34:50.000
COUPLE WILL GET DIVORCED

00:34:50.000 --> 00:34:51.000
EVENTUALLY.

00:34:51.000 --> 00:34:54.000
AND SHE SCORES EIGHT.

00:34:54.000 --> 00:34:55.000
Reporter: GOTTMAN NOW DOES

00:34:55.000 --> 00:34:57.000
WHAT HE CALLS THE INTERVENTION.

00:34:57.000 --> 00:34:58.000
CAN I HELP HERE

00:34:58.000 --> 00:34:59.000
BECAUSE I REALLY THINK --

00:34:59.000 --> 00:35:00.000
Reporter: HE ASKS ALLISON

00:35:00.000 --> 00:35:02.000
THE EXPLAIN WHY SHE HATES

00:35:02.000 --> 00:35:04.000
THE IDEA OF LIVING IN A TRAILER.

00:35:04.000 --> 00:35:05.000
BASICALLY WHAT I'M SAYING

00:35:05.000 --> 00:35:07.000
TO HER IS DON'T DISENGAGE.

00:35:07.000 --> 00:35:08.000
TELL HIM WHAT THIS MEANS TO YOU.

00:35:08.000 --> 00:35:09.000
THAT'S WHAT THE INTERVENTION IS.

00:35:09.000 --> 00:35:10.000
WHAT ARE THE DREAMS BEHIND

00:35:10.000 --> 00:35:12.000
THE CONFLICT?

00:35:12.000 --> 00:35:13.000
Reporter: THIS TIME ALLISON

00:35:13.000 --> 00:35:16.000
GETS TO THE ESSENCE OF IT.

00:35:16.000 --> 00:35:17.000
I LIVED IN THE PROJECTS.

00:35:17.000 --> 00:35:19.000
I DON'T WANT TO GO BACK TO THAT,

00:35:19.000 --> 00:35:22.000
LIVING POOR.

00:35:22.000 --> 00:35:25.000
I DON'T WANT TO GO BACK TO THAT.

00:35:25.000 --> 00:35:26.000
I DON'T WANT TO HAVE TO GO

00:35:26.000 --> 00:35:29.000
TO THE BATHROOM USING

00:35:29.000 --> 00:35:31.000
A FLASHLIGHT.

00:35:31.000 --> 00:35:34.000
I DID THAT.

00:35:34.000 --> 00:35:35.000
NOW THEY'RE STARTING TO TALK

00:35:35.000 --> 00:35:36.000
ABOUT WHAT THEY REALLY FEEL.

00:35:36.000 --> 00:35:37.000
THE PASSION COMES BACK.

00:35:37.000 --> 00:35:38.000
AND SOMETIMES IT'S ANGER.

00:35:38.000 --> 00:35:39.000
Reporter: YOU'RE BRINGING UP

00:35:39.000 --> 00:35:40.000
A LOT OF RAW STUFF, THEY COULD

00:35:40.000 --> 00:35:41.000
START SCREAMING AT EACH OTHER.

00:35:41.000 --> 00:35:42.000
THIS IS USEFUL?

00:35:42.000 --> 00:35:45.000
YES.

00:35:45.000 --> 00:35:46.000
IN THE FIRST DISCUSSION WHEN

00:35:46.000 --> 00:35:48.000
THERE WASN'T THAT SCREAMING RAW

00:35:48.000 --> 00:35:50.000
STUFF, WHAT WE SAW WAS VERY BIG

00:35:50.000 --> 00:35:51.000
PREDICTORS OF DIVORCE.

00:35:51.000 --> 00:35:52.000
Reporter: A LOUD FIGHT IS

00:35:52.000 --> 00:35:54.000
BETTER?

00:35:54.000 --> 00:35:56.000
A LOUD FIGHT WHERE THERE'S

00:35:56.000 --> 00:35:58.000
NO CONTEMPT, YES.

00:35:58.000 --> 00:36:00.000
GO AHEAD, TELL ME I'M MANIAC!

00:36:00.000 --> 00:36:02.000
GO AHEAD, SAY ANYTHING YOU WANT,

00:36:02.000 --> 00:36:03.000
BUT I DON'T CARE!

00:36:03.000 --> 00:36:05.000
I DON'T CARE.

00:36:05.000 --> 00:36:06.000
THAT'S THE WAY I FEEL!

00:36:06.000 --> 00:36:07.000
Reporter: THE CRAMDENS, SAYS

00:36:07.000 --> 00:36:08.000
GOTTMAN, ARE AN EXAMPLE

00:36:08.000 --> 00:36:09.000
OF A HEALTHY COUPLE.

00:36:09.000 --> 00:36:11.000
I LOVE YOU.

00:36:11.000 --> 00:36:12.000
Reporter: FIGHTING AND ANGER,

00:36:12.000 --> 00:36:12.000
HE SAYS, ARE NOT PREDICTORS

00:36:12.000 --> 00:36:15.000
OF DIVORCE.

00:36:15.000 --> 00:36:16.000
MARRIAGES END WITH A WHIMPER.

00:36:16.000 --> 00:36:17.000
PEOPLE GROW APART, THEY'RE

00:36:17.000 --> 00:36:19.000
NO LONGER FRIENDS.

00:36:19.000 --> 00:36:21.000
THEY GET LONELY AND EVENTUALLY

00:36:21.000 --> 00:36:23.000
THERE'S NO CONNECTION.

00:36:23.000 --> 00:36:24.000
Reporter: GOTTMAN DOES

00:36:24.000 --> 00:36:25.000
A SECOND INTERVENTION.

00:36:25.000 --> 00:36:27.000
HE TELLS THEM WHAT HE SAW

00:36:27.000 --> 00:36:28.000
AND SUGGESTS COUNSELING.

00:36:28.000 --> 00:36:29.000
WHAT I WAS WORRIED ABOUT,

00:36:29.000 --> 00:36:30.000
A LITTLE BIT, LISTENING

00:36:30.000 --> 00:36:31.000
TO YOU WAS THAT MAYBE IT WAS TOO

00:36:31.000 --> 00:36:34.000
LATE.

00:36:34.000 --> 00:36:36.000
YOU KNOW, THAT IN A LOT OF WAYS

00:36:36.000 --> 00:36:37.000
YOU'VE LEFT.

00:36:37.000 --> 00:36:40.000
PARTS OF YOU HAVE GONE ALREADY.

00:36:40.000 --> 00:36:41.000
AND YOU'RE GOING TO HAVE TO WORK

00:36:41.000 --> 00:36:42.000
HARD TO REALLY HAVE THE COURAGE

00:36:42.000 --> 00:36:45.000
TO COME BACK AND TRY.

00:36:45.000 --> 00:36:46.000
Reporter: I TALKED TO THEM

00:36:46.000 --> 00:36:49.000
TWO WEEKS LATER.

00:36:49.000 --> 00:36:50.000
THEY SAY THINGS ARE MUCH BETTER.

00:36:50.000 --> 00:36:51.000
DID GOTTMAN'S INTERVENTION HAVE

00:36:51.000 --> 00:36:53.000
SOMETHING TO DO WITH CHANGING

00:36:53.000 --> 00:36:54.000
THE WAY YOU FEEL ABOUT

00:36:54.000 --> 00:36:56.000
THE CONFLICT?

00:36:56.000 --> 00:36:57.000
WE WERE FORCED TO TALK

00:36:57.000 --> 00:36:59.000
ABOUT THE STUFF THAT WE HAD BEEN

00:36:59.000 --> 00:37:01.000
HIDING OR GLOSSING OVER.

00:37:01.000 --> 00:37:01.000
Reporter: GONNA STAY MARRIED?

00:37:01.000 --> 00:37:03.000
OH, YEAH.

00:37:03.000 --> 00:37:10.000
* YOU LIKE POTATO

00:37:10.000 --> 00:37:15.000
* YOU LIKE TO MATE OH -- *

00:37:15.000 --> 00:37:16.000
Reporter: GOTTMAN TRIES

00:37:16.000 --> 00:37:17.000
TO GET COUPLES TO UNDERSTAND

00:37:17.000 --> 00:37:18.000
THAT MANY MARITAL PROBLEMS

00:37:18.000 --> 00:37:19.000
CANNOT BE FIXED.

00:37:19.000 --> 00:37:19.000
YOU JUST NEED TO LEARN TO LIVE

00:37:19.000 --> 00:37:20.000
WITH THEM.

00:37:20.000 --> 00:37:21.000
I DIDN'T GET THAT.

00:37:21.000 --> 00:37:22.000
I DIDN'T GET THAT.

00:37:22.000 --> 00:37:22.000
THAT'S BECAUSE YOU NEVER

00:37:22.000 --> 00:37:23.000
LISTEN.

00:37:23.000 --> 00:37:24.000
IT SEEMS LIKE THE GOAL

00:37:24.000 --> 00:37:25.000
OF COUPLES IS IF THEY SOLVE

00:37:25.000 --> 00:37:26.000
THEIR PROBLEMS, THEY'LL BE

00:37:26.000 --> 00:37:26.000
HAPPY.

00:37:26.000 --> 00:37:27.000
THE GOAL OF THERAPY OUGHT TO BE,

00:37:27.000 --> 00:37:28.000
TO GET COUPLES TO COME TO TERMS

00:37:28.000 --> 00:37:30.000
WITH UNRESOLVABLE ISSUES,

00:37:30.000 --> 00:37:30.000
WITH PERPETUAL PROBLEMS THAT

00:37:30.000 --> 00:37:32.000
THEY'RE GOING TO HAVE FOREVER.

00:37:32.000 --> 00:37:33.000
EVERYTHING HAS TO BE

00:37:33.000 --> 00:37:35.000
SPOTLESS.

00:37:35.000 --> 00:37:36.000
I'M A SPOTTER.

00:37:36.000 --> 00:37:37.000
I'M USED TO IT.

00:37:37.000 --> 00:37:42.000
**

00:37:42.000 --> 00:37:45.000
* AND YOU SAY -- *

00:37:45.000 --> 00:37:46.000
Reporter: THE GOTTMANS TELL

00:37:46.000 --> 00:37:47.000
COUPLES IT'S OKAY THAT YOU CAN'T

00:37:47.000 --> 00:37:48.000
AGREE AND COUPLES OFTEN FIND

00:37:48.000 --> 00:37:49.000
THAT A RELIEF.

00:37:49.000 --> 00:37:50.000
AFTER ALL IF YOU THINK

00:37:50.000 --> 00:37:51.000
ABOUT IT, THERE'S NO HUMAN

00:37:51.000 --> 00:37:53.000
RELATIONSHIP THAT ANY OF US HAVE

00:37:53.000 --> 00:37:54.000
WITH SIBLINGS OR WITH FRIENDS

00:37:54.000 --> 00:37:56.000
THAT IS PERFECT.

00:37:56.000 --> 00:37:58.000
INSTEAD, WE ACCEPT OUR FRIENDS

00:37:58.000 --> 00:37:59.000
WITH NO LIMITATIONS AND THAT'S

00:37:59.000 --> 00:37:59.000
WHAT OUR COUPLES ARE DOING

00:37:59.000 --> 00:38:01.000
IN MARRIAGES THAT ARE WORKING

00:38:01.000 --> 00:38:05.000
VERY WELL.

00:38:05.000 --> 00:38:08.000
YOU ARE, INDEED, MY VERY LIFE

00:38:08.000 --> 00:38:09.000
AND I AM BLESSED TO BE

